instance LightingActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
  base:desc "Ditto device actuator managed by DittoConnectionForLighting, controlled through UnrealTwinController, receives on/off, brightness, colourTempKelvin commands via Eclipse Hono/Ditto"
]

instance LightingCommandSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
  base:desc "Sensor generating lighting command data transmissions"
  DTDFVocab:producedData LightingCommandTransmission
]

instance LightingCommandTransmission : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
  base:desc "Transmission of lighting command data over Eclipse Hono/Ditto"
]

instance LightingCommandData : DTDFVocab:Data [
  base:desc "JSON payload of lighting control command (on, brightness %, colourTempKelvin) published over Eclipse Hono/Ditto"
  DTDFVocab:inputTo DittoConnectionForLighting
  DTDFVocab:fromData LightingCommandTransmission
]

instance DittoConnectionForLighting : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
  base:desc "DittoConnection layer maintaining connectivity and event history for the LightingActuator, integrates with Eclipse Ditto and Hono message broker"
  DTDFVocab:enables LightingControlService
]

instance LightingControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
  base:desc "Service exposing control commands for lighting fixtures, performs safety validation of command values against predefined ranges and communicates via Ditto’s REST interface"
  DTDFVocab:provides AdjustLightingAction
]

instance AdjustLightingAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
  base:desc "Desired operation to turn lights on/off, set brightness percentage, or adjust colour temperature in Kelvin, validated by Ditto policy before execution"
  DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

instance BuildingGeometricModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
  base:desc "Geometric representation of the commercial building rendered in Unreal Engine via TwinComponent objects, derived from enriched BIM (Revit/IFC) with embedded device specifications"
  DTDFVocab:inputTo DittoRegistryEnabler
]

instance BuildingControlLogicSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
  base:desc "Sensor generating building control logic transmissions from building geometry model"
  DTDFVocab:producedData BuildingControlLogicTransmission
]

instance BuildingControlLogicTransmission : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
  base:desc "Transmission of building control logic data over Eclipse Hono/Ditto"
]

instance BuildingControlLogicData : DTDFVocab:Data [
  base:desc "Structured JSON of control logic embedded in BIM (on, brightness, colourTempKelvin properties) for building management"
  DTDFVocab:inputTo DittoRegistryEnabler
  DTDFVocab:fromData BuildingControlLogicTransmission
]

instance DittoRegistryEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
  base:desc "Ditto registry enabler synchronizing BIM topology with Ditto device registry, ensuring real‑time alignment of physical and digital states"
  DTDFVocab:enables BuildingSyncService
]

instance BuildingSyncService : DTDFVocab:Service [
  base:desc "Service orchestrating continuous synchronization between BIM-derived models and Ditto, leveraging Eclipse Hono for data exchange"
  DTDFVocab:provides SyncStatusInsight
]

instance SyncStatusInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
  base:desc "Insight reporting the status of BIM‑Ditto synchronization and any data consistency issues"
]

instance DeviceMetadataSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
  base:desc "Sensor generating device metadata transmissions from registry enabler"
  DTDFVocab:producedData DeviceMetadataTransmission
]

instance DeviceMetadataTransmission : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
  base:desc "Transmission of device metadata over Eclipse Ditto"
]

instance DeviceMetadataData : DTDFVocab:Data [
  base:desc "Descriptive metadata for each physical asset captured in Eclipse Ditto device models, stored and queried through Ditto"
  DTDFVocab:inputTo DittoRegistryEnabler
  DTDFVocab:fromData DeviceMetadataTransmission
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Digital twin instances support real‑time monitoring and control of physical assets. Building Control Engineers use BIM tools to model devices and initiate deployment, while Facility Managers interact with the deployed digital twin for monitoring and issuing control commands. The specific command types, message formats, and authentication mechanisms are not detailed in the documents."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system follows a centralized hub architecture, where the DT Framework serves as the core orchestrator. It is modular, composed of standardized extension points that allow integration of custom analytics and services. Runtime configuration management is employed to adapt the twin’s behavior without full redeployment, enabling high adaptability. Bidirectional data exchange between the physical building and its digital twin is facilitated through this central hub, ensuring that simulation, analysis, and optimization routines are coordinated across all components."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Initialization: Building Control Engineers enrich BIM models with device (sensor, actuator, controller) definitions and control logic, creating a unified semantic representation. Transformation: The model‑driven framework applies MDE principles to extract a structured, machine‑processable representation from the enriched BIM and automatically compiles deployable DT artifacts with minimal manual steps. Deployment and Runtime: The generated artifacts are provisioned into the DT platform, establishing continuous real‑time data exchange with the physical building for synchronization. Operation: Facility Managers monitor and control building operations via interactive, immersive visualizations provided by the DT. Governance: Lifecycle management is anchored in the framework’s modular architecture with standardized extension points, enabling configuration, versioning, and evolution of DT services over time."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model fidelity and data validity are enforced through multiple layers of validation and robustness mechanisms. The MDE pipeline validates the enriched BIM against architectural and device schemas before generating the twin artefacts. Eclipse Ditto’s policy‑based validation guarantees that incoming sensor data and actuator commands conform to defined units and acceptable ranges, eliminating erroneous inputs. Fault tolerance is achieved by Eclipse Hono’s at‑least‑once message delivery semantics, ensuring that no sensor or command message is lost even during network disruptions, complemented by Ditto’s persistent event storage that retains a complete, ordered history of device states for replay and audit. Pre‑execution checks in Ditto prevent the execution of unsafe actuator commands, while the continuous synchronization between the physical building and the Unreal Engine 5 scene provides real‑time verification of twin behaviour against observable reality. These layered safeguards collectively support operational safety, data integrity, and reliable digital‑physical convergence."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin framework provides a bidirectional data exchange capability between the physical assets and the digital model, operating in real‑time. While the documents emphasize robust connectivity and standard compliance, specific network protocols, topology, bandwidth, latency, reliability, redundancy, or security mechanisms are not disclosed."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The framework achieves horizontal integration by exposing standardized extension points that enable the attachment of external services and analytics. It supports interoperability across heterogeneous systems, allowing integration with BIM tools for device modeling, as well as with facility management tools for real‑time monitoring and control. The modular architecture permits coupling with other Digital Twins or enterprise systems, facilitating data exchange through the shared DT Framework hub."
]